parameters: \nc<Advertiser>Well then... that concludes today's advertising shoot!
\nc<Advertiser>Oh my, I must say, this is quite impressive.

\ncWhen the employees started gathering people with just four
people, I honestly had my doubts, but I never expected such
famous people to come.
\nc<Advertiser>Thanks to you, we were able to take a great advertisement!

\nc<>I-I'm still far from being good enough. But if we were able
to capture something good, then I'm glad.

\nc<>Oh! This is just normal, President. If you'd like, you can
leave it to me again next time!

\ncHaha! I'm really happy that both of you said that. After a
while--
\nc<Employee>President~! Can you please check this for me~?

\ncOh, excuse me. I would like to talk a little more with both
of you, but it seems there is still work left to do.

\ncSince both of your work is finished, you can take a rest
here and leave whenever you like.

\nc<>Wow, I never expected to meet Levantia-chan here. It's been
a while, how have you been?

\nc<>That's good then. Even though I may not look like it, I was
worried, you know?

\nc<>After that, I invited them to collaborate on live streams
several times, but they politely declined all of them.

\nc<>I-I've been a little busy. There were things like defeating
villains and stuff.

\nc<>I guess so. After all, they even abandoned the live stream
to go defeat villains. Right?

\nc<>(Oh no, after running away like that, of all places, to meet
here...)

\nc<>(There's no way I can say the reason was because it seemed
suspicious and declined the collaboration stream...!)

\nc<>Well, let's stop with the mean jokes. Seriously, how about
we do a stream together after such a long time?

\nc<>Huh, even though we did that kind of thing, you're inviting
me again?

\nc<>Actually, I haven't suffered that much. Besides, you're
quite popular right now.

\nc<>I can't believe you got a job like this and still have no
awareness.
\nc<>No, it's not like that. I mean, I just can't feel it.
\nc<>I don't really understand why you like me so much...

\nc<>That's a unique worry. Well, it's because you have talent,
isn't it?

\nc<>Hey? You have a good-looking face and big breasts. You have
an unmatched talent, don't you?

\nc<>Did you think it was disgusting just now? But this is the
truth. How much do you think it took to grow my channel to
this point?

\nc<>Huh? W-Well, if it's someone like Matsuo-san, umm... about
a year?
\nc<>Buzz! Big miss. The correct answer is... less than 3 months!
\nc<>Huh, no way. In such a short period of time!?

\nc<>I thought you were more experienced? Unfortunately, it's
true.

\nc<>So, how do you think I managed to come this far in such a
short period of time?

\nc<>There's no need to think too hard. Yes, this body, this
face!

\nc<>Basically, if you have a good appearance, it all depends on
luck and effort.
\nc<>Both you and I have talent, talent.
\nc<>I don't understand what Matsuo-san is trying to say.

\nc<>But, is that really all? If you watch the livestream,
you'll understand.

\nc<>Matsuo-san, you really put in serious effort for the
listeners, didn't you?

\nc<>Isn't it the passion for streaming that has made Matsuo-san
what they are now, something that I don't have?
\nc<>(It's strangely tense... or maybe they're angry...?)

\nc<>Oh man, I took a hit. That's right! Just like Levantia-chan
said, my passionate enthusiasm should have been helpful.

\nc<>If Levantia-chan also puts in effort for the fans, they will
surely be rewarded!

\nc<>Oh no, it's already this late. I'll contact you again
another day regarding the collaboration livestream.
\nc<>Well then, I'll go home first. See you next time!
\nc<>Ah, yes. Thank you for your hard work today...!

\nc<>However, after that, I never received an invitation for a
collaboration livestream from Matsuo...
\nc<>I obtained the memory M2: Advice from the senior streamer.

\nc<>Good listeners increased by 7,000, while bad listeners
increased by 3,000.
